RACE.FOOTNOTES: CUGINO got bumped between foes at the start and conceded three lengths to the front before being able to settle into stride, raced four then three wide through the first turn before settling three wide down the backstretch in pursuit from mid pack, went three then two wide through the far turn coming under coaxing near the quarter pole, swung four wide into upper stretch, rallied and was directed inwards once clear of TRIPLE ESPRESSO a furlong out to look the leader in the eye, dug in head to head taking narrow command a sixteenth from home when placing his main danger in tight along the rail, brushed with that foe as that rival came out slightly near the finish and gamely held on by a nostril to prevail. ENLIGHTEN established the front shortly after the start and showed the way in hand along the inside coming under coaxing at the five-sixteenths, took the inside route into upper stretch, dug in under lone threat to the outside and had that rival come in to look him in the eye, was put in tight a sixteenth out along the rail when headed on the bob for command, dug in coming out very slightly and traded brushes to the finish fighting on gamely but was ultimately nosed at the end in a good effort. TRIPLE ESPRESSO broke in at the start and was bumped due to pressure from UNIQUE INSIGHT breaking outwards, raced three wide through the first turn, chased three to four wide coming under coaxing near the quarter pole, swung three wide into upper stretch, weakened in the late stages while along for the show honors. HAMILTON'S WAY tracked the pace along the inside coming under coaxing at the three-eighths, cut the corner into upper stretch, weakened in the late stages. THORNBURY broke in a step at the start and was bumped between foes and pinched out conceding four lengths to the front, chased along the inside from near the rear of the field, got set down angled five wide into upper stretch, had to alter out a path at the three-sixteenths when URGE TO MERGE tipped out in front and passed tired rivals. BOUNTEOUS broke out a step at the start brushing FOUR TOP, chased just off the inside until tucked inside through the far turn, came under coaxing at the five-sixteenths, swung three to four wide into upper stretch and weakened in the late stages. UNIQUE INSIGHT veered out at the start bumping CUGINO out into URGE TO MERGE and in turn THORNBURY against pressure from TRIPLE ESPRESSO breaking inwards, chased two to three wide under coaxing from the five-sixteenths, continued two to three wide into upper stretch and weakened. FOUR TOP got brushed at the start by BOUNTEOUS, chased three then two wide through the first turn and then three to four wide down the backstretch, tucked to the two path through the far turn coaxed along from the three-eighths, went six wide into upper stretch and tired. URGE TO MERGE (IRE) got bumped between foes at the squeezed out at the start conceding six to seven lengths to the front before settling into stride, chased two to three wide coming under coaxing at the three-eighths, swung four wide into upper stretch, tipped out a path at the three-sixteenths forcing THORNBURY to alter out and made no impact. WON TEAM chased along the inside under coaxing from three furlongs out, spun just off the inside into upper stretch, tired. There was a Jockey's Objection by the rider of ENLIGHTEN alleging interference in the stretch from CUGINO. After review, the objection was dismissed and the result was allowed to stand prior to be declared official.

SOLDIER RISING (GB) two to three wide in pursuit settled at the tail of the field, tucked briefly inside through the final turn, got given a notch to work with before being let out swinging three wide into upper stretch, dug in under a drive rallying, then surged late inside the final seventy yards but missed at the end. VERSTAPPEN traded a bump at the start with TIDE OF THE SEA, settled two to three wide leading the main flight as a pair of rivals widened away in front knocking heads, took closer order into the far and final turn and got first jump on the weakening front to take command spinning two to three wide into upper stretch, got set down straightened away, inched away under a drive to the eighth pole, dug in and was caught seventy yards from the finish, ran on to preserve the show honors on the wire. CROSS BORDER coaxed from the gate, tracked the pace along the inside among the main flight, got set down spinning just off the inside into upper stretch, offered up a mild bid. NINEELEVENTURBO two to three wide in pursuit, came under coaxing four wide at the five-sixteenths, swung three wide into upper stretch offering up a bid, then got outfinished in the late stages while running on to the end. LIMITED LIABILITY just off the inside tracking the gap duel from afar near the rear of the field, came under coaxing at the five-sixteenths, angled four wide into upper stretch and offered up a mild kick to close in but was outkicked to the finish. DAUNT chased two to three wide coming under coaxing at the five-sixteenths, angled out six wide into upper stretch, made some headway but was outkicked. SO HIGH (GB) dueled inside of TIDE OF THE SEA widening away from the rest of the field as a pair, came under coaxing at the five-sixteenths and shook off his main pace foe, took the inside route displaced from command, weakened in the final furlong. MARWAD (GB) chased two to three wide under coaxing from the five-sixteenths, swung five wide into upper stretch and offered no response. TIDE OF THE SEA traded a bump with VERSTAPPEN at the start, dueled two to three wide, got shaken off at the five-sixteenths, cut the corner into upper stretch and tired. LOST ARK chased along the inside, tipped to the two path into the far and final turn and faded three furlongs from home, cornered two to three wide into upper stretch and made no impact.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: DREAMPOINT brushed the outside of the gate at the start, settled on the outside, went two then three wide on the turn, swung five wide into the stretch, rallied to make a bid coming to the furlong marker, took the lead inside that marker and prevailed under good handling. ICY FLAVOR showed speed then pressed the pace on the outside, vied in the two path on the turn, took a short lead into upper stretch, led into the final furlong but was overtaken while able to get the place. RUSSI settled off the pace, went around the turn in the two path, shifted three wide near the quarter-pole, moved out in upper stretch and finished with good energy for the show. HE'S GOT IT settled at the rear, saved ground on the turn, swung five wide into upper stretch then moved further out and improved position. VETERANS BEACH settled just off the pace on the outside without cover, ranged up three wide on the turn, made a bid into the stretch, battled under a drive into the final furlong and weakened. KREESA was well placed while rated on the inside, saved ground on the turn, moved out in upper stretch, chased into the final furlong, paused then altered in behind a foe around the sixteenth-pole and finished willingly. BLAME IT ON DADDY settled towards the back, went three wide on the turn, swung six wide into upper stretch then moved further out and lacked the needed response. IMAGE OF QUALITY broke a half-step slow, was taken in hand early then reserved off the pace, went four then three wide on the turn, moved out in upper stretch and failed to rally. THE COBBLER broke a step slow, rushed up under urging then chased the pace, saved ground on the turn, turned into the stretch in the two path, pursued the leaders into the final furlong and weakened. THANK YOU JON showed good speed then set the pace under pressure to his outside, vied along the rail on the turn, lost the lead into upper stretch and gave way then was in tight near the wire.
